snippet: He pasado 4 horas en urgencias por un ataque de asma. Al inicio me atendieron relativamente rápido, el triaje y luego a la sala de tratamientos. Me iban a hacer un RX y cuando me llamaron me estaban nebulizando y no me pudieron llevar pero tampoco me volvieron a llamar. Terminé el tratamiento a las 5am y a las 6:45 la doctora me dice que espera mi RX para darme el alta y ni siquiera me lo habían hecho. He preguntado en varias ocasiones a las enfermeras del puesto de Convencionales y me han dicho que “son unas mandadas” y que depende de los doctores. Terrible, no quería venir porque sabía que tendría que esperar demasiado pero me sentía muy mal y al final he pasado 4 horas en urgencias por algo que se pudo resolver en máximo 2 horas. Nadie viene a urgencias por gusto, terrible experiencia.
user.name: Denisse Montes de Oca

extracted_snippet.translated: I spent 4 hours in the emergency room for an asthma attack. At first they treated me relatively quickly, triage and then to the treatment room. They were going to do an X-ray on me and when they called me they were nebulizing me and they couldn't take me but they didn't call me back either. I finished the treatment at 5am and at 6:45 the doctor told me that she was waiting for my X-ray to discharge me and they hadn't even done it for me. I have asked the nurses at the Conventional station on several occasions and they have told me that “they are errands” and that it depends on the doctors. Terrible, I didn't want to come because I knew I would have to wait too long but I felt very bad and in the end I spent 4 hours in the emergency room for something that could be resolved in a maximum of 2 hours. Nobody comes to the emergency room for pleasure, terrible experience.
